#. <section class="sutta" id="sn9.13"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn9.13:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 9"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 9"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn9.13:0.2"
msgid "1. Vanavagga"
msgstr "1. In the Woods"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn9.13:0.3"
msgid "13. Pākatindriyasutta"
msgstr "13. Undisciplined Faculties"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.204"></a>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.439"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.13:1.1"
msgid ""
"Ekaṃ samayaṃ sambahulā bhikkhū kosalesu viharanti aññatarasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe "
"uddhatā unnaḷā capalā mukharā vikiṇṇavācā muṭṭhassatino asampajānā asamāhitā "
"vibbhantacittā pākatindriyā."
msgstr ""
"Now at that time several mendicants were staying in the Kosalan lands in a "
"certain forest grove. They were restless, insolent, fickle, gossipy, loose-"
"tongued, unmindful, lacking situational awareness and immersion, with "
"straying minds and undisciplined faculties."

msgctxt "sn9.13:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho yā tasmiṃ vanasaṇḍe adhivatthā devatā tesaṃ bhikkhūnaṃ anukampikā "
"atthakāmā te bhikkhū saṃvejetukāmā yena te bhikkhū tenupasaṅkami; "
"upasaṅkamitvā te bhikkhū gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"The deity haunting that forest had compassion for those mendicants, and "
"wanted what’s best for them. So they approached those mendicants wanting to "
"stir them up, and addressed them in verse:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.13:2.1"
msgid "“Sukhajīvino pure āsuṃ,"
msgstr "“The mendicants used to live happily,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.13:2.2"
msgid "bhikkhū gotamasāvakā;"
msgstr "as disciples of Gotama."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.13:2.3"
msgid "Anicchā piṇḍamesanā,"
msgstr "Desireless they sought alms;"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.13:2.4"
msgid "anicchā sayanāsanaṃ;"
msgstr "desireless they used their lodgings."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.13:2.5"
msgid "Loke aniccataṃ ñatvā,"
msgstr "Knowing that the world was impermanent"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.13:2.6"
msgid "dukkhassantaṃ akaṃsu te."
msgstr "they made an end of suffering."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.13:3.1"
msgid "Dupposaṃ katvā attānaṃ,"
msgstr "But now they’ve made themselves hard to look after,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.13:3.2"
msgid "gāme gāmaṇikā viya;"
msgstr "like chiefs in a village."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.13:3.3"
msgid "Bhutvā bhutvā nipajjanti,"
msgstr "They eat and eat and then lie down,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.13:3.4"
msgid "parāgāresu mucchitā."
msgstr "unconscious in the homes of others."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.13:4.1"
msgid "Saṃghassa añjaliṃ katvā,"
msgstr "Having raised my joined palms to the Saṅgha,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.13:4.2"
msgid "idhekacce vadāmahaṃ;"
msgstr "I speak here only about certain people."

#. <br>
#. VAR: Apaviddhā → apaviṭṭhā (s1-3, km) | appaviddhā (pts1)
msgctxt "sn9.13:4.3"
msgid "Apaviddhā anāthā te,"
msgstr "They’re rejects, with no protector,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.13:4.4"
msgid "yathā petā tatheva te."
msgstr "just like those who have passed away."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.13:5.1"
msgid "Ye kho pamattā viharanti,"
msgstr "I’m speaking about"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.13:5.2"
msgid "te me sandhāya bhāsitaṃ;"
msgstr "those who live negligently."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.13:5.3"
msgid "Ye appamattā viharanti,"
msgstr "To those who live diligently"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn9.13:5.4"
msgid "namo tesaṃ karomahan”ti."
msgstr "I pay homage.”"

#. </p></blockquote><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn9.13:6.1"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū tāya devatāya saṃvejitā saṃvegamāpādunti."
msgstr "Stirred up by that deity, those mendicants came to their senses."
